                            <comment id="14460166" author="johnstump" created="Thu, 22 Apr 2004 12:39:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would like to up the priority on this to &quot;Major&quot;, but I don&apos;t know how to edit the bug entry. This is major to me because it is very common in my code (and others I have seen) to have variables the same name as the class they are of, but with different case. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;repository = new Repository()&lt;br/&gt;
version = new Version()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Java supports this, even on the case insensitive Mac FS, so I would like groovy to support this as well...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460304" author="johnstump" created="Wed, 12 May 2004 17:15:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am attaching a patch for this bug. What it does is not use File.exists() because this does not do a case sensitive comparison when looking for files. So I get a list of files from the directory and then search the list using a case sensitive comparison. I have run all the tests and they pass.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch is on CVS head dated 05/12/2004.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460266" author="johnstump" created="Wed, 12 May 2004 22:27:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the patch that fixes this bug...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460365" author="johnstump" created="Thu, 13 May 2004 17:09:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch I attched to this issue may not quite work; I&apos;m having some class loading problems that are more than likely due to this patch. I&apos;m debugging the problem now...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460305" author="johnstump" created="Thu, 13 May 2004 22:32:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an updated patch that actually works this time (imagine that!) I also optimized my original solution to speed it up a little.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14460285" author="spullara" created="Sun, 23 May 2004 16:08:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
